SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04214298
Version: 1

HPSBGN02986 rev.1 - HP IceWall Identity Manager and HP IceWall SSO Password
Reset Option Running Apache Commons FileUpload, Remote Denial of Service
(DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-04-03
Last Updated: 2014-04-03

Potential Security Impact: Remote Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP IceWall
Identity Manager and HP IceWall SSO Password Reset Option Running Apache
Commons FileUpload. The vulnerability could be exploited remotely resulting
in a Denial of Service (DoS).

References: CVE-2014-2600, SSRT101450

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

HP IceWall Identity Manager Version 4.0

HP IceWall Identity Manager Version 4.0SP1

HP IceWall Identity Manager Version 5.0

HP IceWall SSO Version 10.0 Password Reset Option

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-2600    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:S/C:N/I:N/A:P)       4.0
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP IceWall customers can download a procedure to update Apache Commons
FileUpload from the following location:

http://www.hp.com/jp/icewall_patchaccess

Please note that the HP IceWall product is only available in Japan.

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 3 April 2014 Initial release

